content: Even wennen aan deze rijdende computer
content_english:
Even when getting used to this driving computer

(Note: The phrase "Even wennen aan" is an idiomatic expression that can be translated as "Even when getting used to" to preserve the tone and sentiment.)

Even when getting used to this driving computer (iDrive) of the MyBMW App, there's still a lot to discover. The integration with Connected Drive and the Digital Key are pretty neat features. However, sometimes it feels like I'm driving an unfamiliar car. It would be great if the climate control settings could sync better between my phone and the car. Overall, it's a step in the right direction, but there's room for improvement.

[330e (Model Number)]

content: 3 jaar Tiguan gereden, 0 problemen met de App en auto zelf. Nu X3 30e met falende app en auto zelf. Spraakbesturing werkt vaker niet dan wel (bij meerdere personen). Herkent de sleutel/bestuurder vaak niet. Vraagt vaak opnieuw naar inloggegevens. Connected drive is erg onstabiel en daardoor onbetrouwbaar. Via app auto niet terug kunnen vinden! Laadgegevens worden soms dagenlang niet opgeslagen en plotseling wel weer. Ik kan er wel een boek over schrijven. Kan helaas de auto niet teruggeven :-(
content_english:
3 years driving a Tiguan, no problems with the App or the car itself. Now using an X3 30e with failing app and car functionality. Voice control works more often not than yes (by multiple people). Doesn't recognize the key/driver often enough. Frequently asks for login information again. Connected Drive is extremely unstable and therefore unreliable. Via the app, the car cannot be found! Sometimes location data is not saved for days and suddenly it is after a while. I could write a book about it. Unfortunately, I can't return the car :-(
Note: No technical terms or vehicle features required translation as per your guidelines.

content_english: You almost pay an extra €3000 for a Connected Drive navigation system, and then you can't even update your iDrive to a new version. Meanwhile, cheaper manufacturers already offer free over-the-air updates with their standard systems. Both the iDrive in the car and the MyBMW App don't work well and feel amateurishly made. I had higher expectations from this Connected Drive system; it's actually quite outdated. A missed opportunity!

content: De bediening van je autp doet er lang over, meer dan 15 sec, voor lichtjes seinen bijv. De app vraagt regelmatig om opnieuw in te loggen en pincode voor de app in te stellen. Daarnaast is de app nu de auto kwijt. Pagina voor vincode invoer werkt niet. Slechte app voor zo'n degelijke auto. Overigens kun je alleen erbruiksdata van de elektro zien, niet bijv gemiddel erbruik benzine of maandelijks overzicht hoeveel km hoeveel daarvan brandstof/elektrisch. Gemiste kans voor leuke details

Additionally, the app has lost track of the car now. The page for entering the VIN code isn't working. This is a bad app for such a reliable car. By the way, you can only see usage data from electricity consumption; for example, average fuel consumption or monthly overview of how many km are driven with either fuel/electricity. Lost opportunity for cool details.

content: Prima Service
content_english: Prima service experience with the MyBMW App! The Digital Key feature is a game-changer, giving me secure access to my car from anywhere. Charging station locations are easily accessible, and I can monitor my 330e's battery status remotely. Overall, highly recommend this app for any BMW owner!
